ts": 52, "quotes": 4, "bookmarks": 16, "labels": null}, {"id": "2062101131812053088", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2062101131812053088", "text": "Timely reminder that Iran is also under economic pressure due to the war; both sides pretend that they aren't under pressure for a deal, but both Washington and Tehran need a deal sooner than later.", "time": "09:16", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 63580, "likes": 313, "replies": 27, "retweets": 48, "quotes": 4, "bookmarks": 25, "labels": null}, {"id": "2062124495385592262", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2062124495385592262", "text": "Where’s the next problem in refined oil products? \n\nTop commodity trader Vitol says Atlantic Basin refiners have worked very hard to solve the jet fuel (and diesel) problem — but that’s creating a gasoline issue.", "time": "10:49", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 49303, "likes": 385, "replies": 12, "retweets": 52, "quotes": 3, "bookmarks": 33, "labels": null}, {"id": "2062141168159166976", "url": "https://x.com/SXPomerleau/status/2062141168159166691", "text": "What's up with the global oil market? \n\nWhy aren't oil prices skyrocketing? \n\nMy boss @djheakin explained why in today's @AAF Daily Dish. \n\nHe also quoted @Bob_McNally's comments in FT yesterday. (I just found out Doug and Bob used to work together. What a small world!)\n\n#OOTT https://t.co/FnuX3L2Nm", "time": "11:55", "author": "SXPomerleau", "author_name": "Shuting Pomerleau", "followers": 1065, "views": 4205, "likes": 7, "replies": 1, "retweets": 6, "quotes": 2, "bookmarks": 2, "labels": null}, {"id": "2062162187464889088", "url": "https://x.com/SanctionsAml/status/2062162187464888746", "text": "@robin_j_brooks first put out this chart👇 on March 19 2026\n\nWhen markets were in full panic mode\n\nHis point:\n\nPersian Gulf operating at half capacity implied a price rise of 60-80%✅️\n\nWe're at 60% now\n\nSo some rise can occur, but not new highs\n\nhttps://t.co/ZPc5YpSp6s…\n#OOTT", "time": "13:19", "author": "SanctionsAml", "author_name": "SanctionsAML", "followers": 754, "views": 8394, "likes": 14, "replies": 1, "retweets": 5, "quotes": 0, "bookmarks": 6, "labels": null}, {"id": "2062180486814831104", "url": "https://x.com/JuliOnTwtr/status/2062180486814831058", "text": "EIA WPSR Inventory 6/3/26\n\nCrude -8.0 million \nGasoline +3.4 million \nDistillates +1.5 million\n\n#oott #crudeoil #eiawpsr", "time": "14:31", "author": "JuliOnTwtr", "author_name": "Julianne Geiger", "followers": 8462, "views": 9405, "likes": 116, "replies": 5, "retweets": 17, "quotes": 2, "bookmarks": 3, "labels": null}, {"id": "2062180547913289984", "url": "https://x.com/LiveSquawk/status/2062180547913289835", "text": "#OOTT | US DoE Crude Oil Inventories (W/W) 29-May: -7.974M (est -3.050M; prev -3.327M)\n- Distillate: +1.502M (est -1.950M; prev -2.107M)\n- Cushing: -583K (prev -2.794M)\n- Gasoline: +3.364M (est -2.450M; prev -2.572M)\n- Refinery: 0.20% (est 0.22%; prev 2.90%)", "time": "14:32", "author": "LiveSquawk", "author_name": "LiveSquawk", "followers": 407998, "views": 6073, "likes": 12, "replies": 0, "retweets": 5, "quotes": 2, "bookmarks": 2, "labels": null}, {"id": "2062180734689754880", "url": "https://x.com/staunovo/status/2062180734689755402", "text": "US crude inventories fell by 15.967mb last week\n(commercial -7.974mb, SPR -7.993mb) \nEIA #oott", "time": "14:32", "author": "staunovo", "author_name": "Giovanni Staunovo🛢", "followers": 119642, "views": 6133, "likes": 62, "replies": 6, "retweets": 11, "quotes": 2, "bookmarks": 1, "labels": null}, {"id": "2062182949747864064", "url": "https://x.com/OilandEnergy/status/2062182949747864052", "text": "U.S. crude inventories fell by 8 million barrels last week, far exceeding expectations and pushing stockpiles 3% below the five-year average. The draw comes as oil demand remains strong and global supply risks persist. #Oil #EIA #OOTT #EnergyMarkets \n\nhttps://t.co/SaX1VOeT2K", "time": "14:41", "author": "OilandEnergy", "author_name": "OilPrice.com", "followers": 95942, "views": 7978, "likes": 89, "replies": 5, "retweets": 25, "quotes": 1, "bookmarks": 5, "labels": null}, {"id": "2062206115861996032", "url": "https://x.com/profutures2012/status/2062206115861995726", "text": "We have lost 2.5 days of cover in 2.5 months?\n\nI'll swallow my pride and admit...\n\nChina and US admin have played this masterfully so far\n\n#OOTT\n\nIts all band aids and duct tape and will end... but not just yet", "time": "16:13", "author": "profutures2012", "author_name": "Mark Johnston", "followers": 9859, "views": 16900, "likes": 57, "replies": 3, "retweets": 1, "quotes": 0, "bookmarks": 21, "labels": null}, {"id": "2062211355868836096", "url": "https://x.com/staunovo/status/2062211355868836050", "text": "Charts on US petroleum inventories in million barrels (EIA) #oott https://t.co/WUZVAhbtaJ", "time": "16:34", "author": "staunovo", "author_name": "Giovanni Staunovo🛢", "followers": 119641, "views": 17951, "likes": 109, "replies": 4, "retweets": 30, "quotes": 6, "bookmarks": 18, "labels": null}, {"id": "2062221535411085056", "url": "https://x.com/OilandEnergy/status/2062221535411085428", "text": "Markets may be underestimating the post-Hormuz recovery timeline. Kuwait Petroleum says crude production would take up to 12 weeks to fully recover after a reopening, highlighting the risk of prolonged supply tightness. #CrudeOil #OOTT #EnergyMarkets \n\nhttps://t.co/zBW6LRWZGA", "time": "17:15", "author": "OilandEnergy", "author_name": "OilPrice.com", "followers": 95942, "views": 4429, "likes": 49, "replies": 5, "retweets": 17, "quotes": 3, "bookmarks": 3, "labels": null}, {"id": "2062242851149529088", "url": "https://x.com/BokehResearch/status/2062242851149529438", "text": "Kuwait says they can reach 70% oil capacity in ~7 weeks, and the remaining 30% in ~30 days.  That would mean net ~36 days of lost production after the SoH is open.  \n\nExtrapolate to 13.5mbpd of shut-ins across the gulf, it's 484mb of lost production after the SoH opens.\n\n#oott https://t.co/fgjPBR7sw", "time": "18:39", "author": "BokehResearch", "author_name": "BokehResearch", "followers": 346, "views": 22960, "likes": 33, "replies": 3, "retweets": 6, "quotes": 1, "bookmarks": 7, "labels": null}, {"id": "2062248490873360445", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2062248490873360445", "text": "Word of the day: “screwworm.”\n\nThe parasite has been moving north throughout Central America and Mexico. The USDA puts the closest confirmed cases ~25 miles south of the US-Mexican border. \n\nFor many in the cattle industry, it’s a case of when rather than if it reaches the US.", "time": "19:02", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 118479, "likes": 260, "replies": 18, "retweets": 28, "quotes": 6, "bookmarks": 15, "labels": null}, {"id": "2062298614211194880", "url": "https://x.com/aeberman12/status/2062298614211194998", "text": "WTI comparative inventory decreased 7.5 mmb to 29 mmb less than the 5-year average\nfor week ending May 29\n\nWTI price includes a $12 risk premium: \n\ninventories say $81, markets say $93\n#energy #OOTT #oilandgas #WTI #CrudeOil #fintwit #OPEC #Commodities #commoditiesmarket https://t.co/m9WFqJv81Q", "time": "22:21", "author": "aeberman12", "author_name": "Art Berman", "followers": 52885, "views": 2607, "likes": 42, "replies": 4, "retweets": 12, "quotes": 0, "bookmarks": 5, "labels": null}, {"id": "2062310938338877952", "url": "https://x.com/aeberman12/status/2062310938338877776", "text": "The US blockade is \"choking off\" Iran's production?@WoodMackenzie \n\nIran's \"choked off production\" still makes it the 9th largest oil producer in the world.\n\nTry objective reporting.\n\n#energy #OOTT #oilandgas #WTI #CrudeOil #fintwit #OPEC #Commodities #commoditiesmarket https://t.co/teyRdbhUr7", "time": "23:10", "author": "aeberman12", "author